WEBVTT

00:00.542 --> 00:04.041
(Orchestral music)

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.976 --> 00:26.767
(shower running)

00:34.125 --> 00:36.583
[Woman] The key to
being a good mistress,

00:36.667 --> 00:39.208
is to always having
you wanting me,

00:39.291 --> 00:40.458
more than I want you.

00:41.709 --> 00:43.583
It's about the effort
I'm willing to make,

00:43.667 --> 00:46.500
when the other person who's
at home doesn't anymore.

00:47.959 --> 00:50.917
I like making you feel
like the priority.

00:51.834 --> 00:54.458
I'm independent,
financially stable,

00:54.542 --> 00:57.041
and will never be a burden
to you or your family.

00:57.881 --> 00:59.917
My days aren't
filled thinking about

01:00.000 --> 01:01.917
how to make our
relationship work,

01:02.000 --> 01:04.041
how to keep the spark,

01:04.125 --> 01:06.250
or what I need to do to
keep you on the hook.

01:07.417 --> 01:08.959
Of course, there are rules.

01:10.041 --> 01:12.667
Don't put me in situations
that might be risky.

01:12.750 --> 01:15.625
I don't want the accidental
run-ins with your friends,

01:15.709 --> 01:19.625
or to be taken to a restaurant
you go to with your wife.

01:20.822 --> 01:22.750
I don't want to be on the radar.

01:22.834 --> 01:24.709
I'm willing to live
in the shadows,

01:24.792 --> 01:26.250
and I prefer it that way.

01:27.750 --> 01:29.030
I won't be your first phone call

01:29.041 --> 01:30.583
when you and your
wife have a fight.

01:30.667 --> 01:34.500
You have friends for that,
and I am not your backup plan.

01:34.583 --> 01:36.208
Yes, I'm your friend.

01:36.291 --> 01:38.458
I'm happy to listen
and discuss the things

01:38.542 --> 01:40.390
that are important to you,

01:40.414 --> 01:42.573
but I'm not interested in
hearing about the issues

01:42.583 --> 01:44.543
you and your wife deal
with on a day-to-day basis.

01:47.111 --> 01:48.830
When all is said and done,

01:48.896 --> 01:51.500
my hope is that I'm
out of the picture,

01:51.583 --> 01:54.560
and you and your wife will
live happily ever after.

01:55.750 --> 01:58.500
The time we spend
together is our time,

01:58.583 --> 02:00.750
but when we're separate,
we're separate.

02:00.834 --> 02:03.333
You have your life
and I have mine.

02:04.625 --> 02:07.205
I'm the only one, there
will be no others.

02:07.216 --> 02:11.000
There will be no expensive
gifts or money exchanged.

02:11.083 --> 02:12.709
We don't do holidays.

02:12.792 --> 02:13.834
As far as I'm concerned,

02:13.917 --> 02:16.500
Christmas should be
celebrated with your family,

02:16.583 --> 02:17.583
not with me.

02:22.166 --> 02:24.641
But the most important
rule of them all,

02:25.166 --> 02:26.709
I am not your possession.

02:27.792 --> 02:30.407
So you'll treat me, and my time,

02:30.979 --> 02:32.104
with respect.

02:38.432 --> 02:41.599
Have I told you how
incredible you look tonight?

02:41.792 --> 02:43.750
You have Nathan,
thank you again.

02:44.667 --> 02:47.125
So, the last time
we were together,

02:47.208 --> 02:49.583
I was telling you about that
deal, the Jamison Merger?

02:49.667 --> 02:51.083
Oh yes, that's right.

02:51.166 --> 02:52.417
Veronica,

02:52.500 --> 02:53.667
I closed it.

02:53.750 --> 02:55.291
Congratulations.

02:55.375 --> 02:57.250
That one was not easy,

02:57.333 --> 02:58.500
but if everything pans out

02:58.583 --> 03:00.709
we'll be opening offices
in Tokyo come August.

03:00.792 --> 03:01.792
Fantastic.

03:03.484 --> 03:05.484
Don't worry, I'll only
be gone a couple of weeks.

03:05.495 --> 03:06.543
(phone buzzing)

03:06.554 --> 03:07.554
Sorry.

03:12.085 --> 03:13.527
What if it's important?

03:13.538 --> 03:14.620
You should take that.

03:14.631 --> 03:16.191
She can wait.

03:16.202 --> 03:19.041
Nathan, you're not
where she thinks you are.

03:19.125 --> 03:20.655
You should answer it.

03:20.666 --> 03:21.671
If I answer that here,

03:21.682 --> 03:24.222
she'll know I'm not
where I'm supposed to be.

03:24.233 --> 03:26.989
Then why don't you go
outside and call her?

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
Now, go on.

03:31.884 --> 03:34.553
Order us another bottle,
I'll be right back.

03:39.967 --> 03:42.208
Look I told you I
couldn't be interrupted

03:42.291 --> 03:44.375
while I was meeting
with these investors.

03:44.458 --> 03:45.458
What's up?

03:47.523 --> 03:49.356
Say again?

03:49.367 --> 03:50.825
You what?

03:56.130 --> 03:58.005
[Veronica] Is everything okay?

03:58.166 --> 03:59.166
I have to go.

04:00.224 --> 04:01.640
Why Nathan?

04:01.651 --> 04:03.817
I'm sorry we didn't get
to have dinner together,

04:03.828 --> 04:06.350
but at least we got
to share some wine.

04:09.333 --> 04:10.875
I took care of the bill.

04:11.000 --> 04:12.663
I'll call you tomorrow.

04:13.583 --> 04:15.500
(soft jazz piano)

04:18.333 --> 04:20.375
(doorbell ringing)

04:22.208 --> 04:23.667
Hi, Ian.

04:23.750 --> 04:26.333
Wow, Veronica, you look amazing.

04:26.417 --> 04:29.625
Oh you're so sweet,
how much do I owe you?

04:29.709 --> 04:32.387
Uh it's gonna be $17.63.

04:32.583 --> 04:33.917
Keep the change.

04:35.000 --> 04:36.042
Thanks.

04:36.750 --> 04:38.417
So did you just get
dressed up for me,

04:38.500 --> 04:40.207
or what's the occasion?

04:40.218 --> 04:42.008
No occasion.

04:42.019 --> 04:43.782
My evening just ended early.

04:43.793 --> 04:44.845
If I was taking you out,

04:44.856 --> 04:47.064
the evening wouldn't end early.

04:47.291 --> 04:50.041
You know I'm old
enough to be your mother?

04:50.125 --> 04:51.333
So?

04:51.417 --> 04:53.500
I live enough on
the edge as it is, go.

04:55.917 --> 04:56.917
Bye Veronica.

05:00.359 --> 05:02.734
[Man On TV] <i>Gonna have
a talk with the President.</i>

05:02.959 --> 05:05.375
[Man On TV] <i>Oh, telling
him we're gonna rob him?</i>

05:05.458 --> 05:06.542
<i>Not a good idea, man.</i>

05:06.625 --> 05:09.208
[Man On TV] <i>I'm not
telling, you idiot.</i>

05:09.760 --> 05:11.724
[Man On TV] <i>Oh, you're the
one stealing from the mob,</i>

05:11.734 --> 05:13.484
<i>but I'm the idiot?</i>

05:14.917 --> 05:16.500
[Man On TV] <i>Point taken.</i>

05:16.583 --> 05:20.333
<i>All right man, good
luck, you outta here?</i>

05:20.417 --> 05:21.615
[Woman On TV] <i>You get caught,</i>

05:21.625 --> 05:24.041
<i>your father, he may
forgive you, but not--</i>

05:24.125 --> 05:29.208
<i>Touch, touch, touch, touch,
touch, touch, get up there,</i>

05:29.917 --> 05:32.291
<i>touch, touch, out and hold.</i>

05:32.302 --> 05:33.322
<i>Hold.</i>

05:33.333 --> 05:34.417
<i>Hold.</i>

05:34.500 --> 05:35.917
<i>Another two is now, let's go.</i>

05:36.000 --> 05:38.583
<i>Come on, you're better today
than you were yesterday,</i>

05:38.667 --> 05:41.083
<i>but not as good as you'll
be tomorrow, come on.</i>

05:43.125 --> 05:46.583
(phone ringing)

05:48.756 --> 05:50.072
Ronnie, can you get that?

05:50.083 --> 05:50.792
(phone ringing)

05:50.875 --> 05:52.208
Just coming.

05:55.083 --> 05:56.834
Bookaneer, can I help you?

05:58.192 --> 05:59.850
Oh, hi Margie.

06:01.255 --> 06:03.255
Oh, let me ask Trent,
hold on one sec.

06:03.417 --> 06:04.125
Trent?

06:04.208 --> 06:05.991
Did Margie's order come in yet?

06:06.002 --> 06:08.639
Just, it's in the drawer
with her name on it.

06:11.000 --> 06:13.343
Yep, it's right here.

06:14.667 --> 06:19.835
Uh, no no, you can come in
tomorrow anytime after 10.

06:19.846 --> 06:20.513
No, no no.

06:20.524 --> 06:22.856
Right, bye bye.

06:24.129 --> 06:25.836
No no no no no,
you call her back.

06:25.847 --> 06:27.138
Why?

06:27.166 --> 06:28.365
You're meeting Adam tomorrow

06:28.375 --> 06:30.250
at the Summerland
Estate at 11 o'clock.

06:30.333 --> 06:31.458
You can handle Margie.

06:31.542 --> 06:34.166
Just because I can,
doesn't mean I want to.

06:34.250 --> 06:35.000
I know.

06:35.083 --> 06:36.458
You do know, don't you?

06:36.542 --> 06:38.333
You're enjoying
this, aren't you?

06:38.934 --> 06:39.959
She's fun.

06:40.041 --> 06:41.581
She's awful.

06:41.592 --> 06:44.471
I'm not even in the front door, and
you two are making fun of my outfit.

06:44.482 --> 06:45.250
Hi, hon.

06:45.261 --> 06:46.072
Hey Brandon.

06:46.083 --> 06:46.987
What did I miss?

06:46.998 --> 06:49.849
I'll fill you in at lunch, I'm
just gonna go get my purse.

06:57.625 --> 06:59.625
Great, now we can charge double.

06:59.636 --> 07:01.238
I'll make sure Ronnie
gets a couple of more copies

07:01.248 --> 07:02.406
for you guys next week.

07:02.417 --> 07:05.166
What we really need, is for
you to do an in-store signing,

07:05.177 --> 07:07.061
it would really
liven up the joint.

07:07.072 --> 07:08.675
It's not my thing.

07:09.041 --> 07:10.041
Could be.

07:10.851 --> 07:12.542
Ready.

07:12.965 --> 07:15.212
So, am I losing you for
the rest of the afternoon?

07:15.223 --> 07:17.583
You're not gonna close
up early again, are you?

07:17.667 --> 07:19.917
That happened once,
and it was an emergency.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.166
No, I wanted to show
you my new routine.

07:22.250 --> 07:23.667
Oh, we certainly
can't miss that.

07:23.750 --> 07:26.500
Honey, I'm gonna be
there, later tonight.

07:26.511 --> 07:28.009
It's okay Trent,
I'll have her back

07:28.020 --> 07:29.239
in a couple of hours.

07:29.250 --> 07:30.834
Don't forget my doggie bag.

07:30.917 --> 07:31.792
(bell ringing)

07:31.875 --> 07:32.875
Woof.

07:37.461 --> 07:38.461
Woof.

07:39.625 --> 07:41.625
So, how was your date?

07:41.709 --> 07:43.125
He left before dinner.

07:43.918 --> 07:45.751
Oh, how are we
feeling about this?

07:46.100 --> 07:48.633
It's conflicted, you know.

07:48.761 --> 07:51.719
I know I ought to feel
mad, but I don't and,

07:51.730 --> 07:54.564
feel a little bit
jealous, and I shouldn't.

07:54.714 --> 07:56.823
Jealous about what, exactly?

07:58.709 --> 08:01.166
About my place, and
list of priorities.

08:02.166 --> 08:03.166
I get that.

08:04.750 --> 08:05.792
But he is married.

08:05.875 --> 08:07.542
I know, and I accept
that but sometimes

08:07.625 --> 08:10.252
it's harder than
others to understand.

08:12.000 --> 08:13.514
So you like this guy?

08:14.168 --> 08:16.698
As much as I like any
of the guys I go out with.

08:16.709 --> 08:18.375
So, not enough.

08:18.458 --> 08:20.584
What's that supposed to mean?

08:21.083 --> 08:24.186
Am I supposed to want to
break up their marriage?

08:25.500 --> 08:26.709
I want you to care enough

08:26.792 --> 08:29.208
that you'd want them
to only be with you.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.959
Is that what you would've
liked when we were dating?

08:33.008 --> 08:35.364
Well, I would have been
the cause of your divorce,

08:35.375 --> 08:38.375
and then we couldn't be the
friends that we are right now.

08:38.457 --> 08:40.384
You didn't cause my divorce.

08:40.808 --> 08:42.143
My marriage did.

08:46.458 --> 08:48.917
Hey, my grandnephew's
birthday's next week.

08:49.000 --> 08:50.680
Can you help me pick
out a present for him?

08:50.750 --> 08:52.353
Great, how old is he?

08:53.959 --> 08:55.375
Seven, I think.

08:58.521 --> 09:00.961
No, I'm sorry that
title's out of print.

09:01.500 --> 09:02.598
Yeah, even in paperback.

09:02.609 --> 09:04.401
Out of print, is out of print.

09:04.412 --> 09:05.456
(bell ringing)

09:05.467 --> 09:07.409
Okay, oh gotta go.

09:07.542 --> 09:09.398
All right, thank you.

09:09.583 --> 09:10.583
Ho ho ho.

09:11.250 --> 09:12.640
Beg, beg.

09:13.959 --> 09:17.125
Ah, Portofino Italian
Bistro, my favorite.

09:17.208 --> 09:18.208
Thank you.

09:19.375 --> 09:20.375
Thanks for lunch.

09:20.417 --> 09:21.792
My pleasure.

09:21.875 --> 09:23.834
Thanks for helping me
pick out a gift for Bobby.

09:24.750 --> 09:25.959
Movie tonight?

09:26.041 --> 09:28.015
[Trent] Ronnie, my
showcase is tonight.

09:28.026 --> 09:30.137
I guess that answers that,
do you want to join us?

09:30.148 --> 09:31.698
I have to take a rain check.

09:32.375 --> 09:33.375
Sure.

09:33.458 --> 09:35.338
Hey, I'm going up the
coast to San Luis Obispo

09:35.375 --> 09:37.120
to scout for my new book.

09:37.792 --> 09:38.792
Wanna go?

09:38.875 --> 09:40.115
I love our trips, yeah, I'm in.

09:40.125 --> 09:41.458
Great.

09:41.542 --> 09:43.750
(phone notification)

09:47.562 --> 09:48.546
What?

09:48.557 --> 09:49.445
Nothing.

09:49.456 --> 09:50.456
Okay.

09:51.333 --> 09:52.625
What?

09:52.636 --> 09:53.882
Nothing.

09:53.937 --> 09:55.823
Have fun tonight.

09:55.834 --> 09:56.834
Bye.

09:59.083 --> 10:00.146
What?

10:00.157 --> 10:02.825
Nothing, go, do,
I'll see you later.

10:04.834 --> 10:06.166
(bell ringing)

10:06.250 --> 10:09.250
(soft piano music)

10:47.959 --> 10:49.542
I'm glad you
could make it today.

10:49.625 --> 10:51.901
Thank you for arranging this.

10:51.912 --> 10:53.407
The vultures will
pillage everything

10:53.417 --> 10:55.375
but the paint from the
walls when they arrive.

10:56.130 --> 10:59.255
But you get carte blanche.

11:05.993 --> 11:07.244
In here.

11:07.476 --> 11:09.017
Why?

11:09.117 --> 11:11.827
You know how I always
take care of you.

11:15.134 --> 11:17.051
Love is a smoke

11:17.166 --> 11:19.041
raised with the fume of sighs,

11:20.323 --> 11:23.740
being purged, the fires
sparkling in lovers' eyes.

11:24.910 --> 11:29.082
Being vexed, a scene
nourished with lovers' tears.

11:29.500 --> 11:30.583
What is it else?

11:31.166 --> 11:33.208
A madness most discreet.

11:34.002 --> 11:35.128
A choking gall.

11:35.171 --> 11:36.546
And a preserving sweet.

11:38.884 --> 11:39.884
You know this?

11:40.750 --> 11:42.851
Of course, Romeo and Juliet.

11:44.208 --> 11:45.913
The forbidden lovers.

11:48.500 --> 11:50.710
Have a drink with me tonight.

11:52.437 --> 11:55.578
Adam, you're married,
and I'm seeing someone.

11:57.523 --> 12:00.041
You know I'll keep
asking until you say yes.

12:00.125 --> 12:01.625
And history has proven that.

12:02.640 --> 12:04.182
Well, points for persistence.

12:06.117 --> 12:08.242
Help me, I want to get
these to the store.

12:15.347 --> 12:17.750
Oh Ronnie, we really
hit the jackpot here.

12:17.834 --> 12:19.433
Tell me about it.

12:20.554 --> 12:23.096
(bell ringing)

12:24.500 --> 12:25.792
Hi Margie.

12:25.875 --> 12:27.291
Good day, my dear.

12:27.375 --> 12:28.750
Hello Trent.

12:28.834 --> 12:29.834
Hello.

12:31.250 --> 12:32.817
There you go.

12:32.864 --> 12:33.947
It's for my grandson.

12:33.958 --> 12:36.667
Oh, it's very mature reading.

12:36.750 --> 12:38.630
Well, Lord knows I don't
want him falling prey

12:38.709 --> 12:41.166
to the liberal down slide.

12:41.250 --> 12:42.597
What is he, eight?

12:42.608 --> 12:45.816
Yes, a very impressionable age.

12:45.827 --> 12:47.369
So, what do I owe you?

12:47.380 --> 12:49.546
45 dollars and 87 cents please.

12:51.094 --> 12:54.719
I have exact change.

12:55.013 --> 12:56.432
Of course you do.

12:57.817 --> 12:59.026
Here it is.

12:59.500 --> 13:02.083
Now, when are you
getting married?

13:02.166 --> 13:06.333
Ah, well just as soon as
I find Mister Right, Margie.

13:06.417 --> 13:07.421
When you stop looking,

13:07.432 --> 13:09.030
that's when you're
going to find him.

13:09.041 --> 13:11.667
You know I met Harold
when I was on a train trip

13:11.750 --> 13:14.250
in Europe with my sister, Edna.

13:14.929 --> 13:16.875
Oh, that is so romantic.

13:16.959 --> 13:18.875
I met my Steve on a train.

13:18.959 --> 13:20.250
We got married last month.

13:21.750 --> 13:24.125
Thank you for the book, dear.

13:26.458 --> 13:28.125
(bell ringing)

13:28.208 --> 13:29.625
Really? On a train?

13:29.709 --> 13:31.375
I couldn't resist.

13:31.386 --> 13:33.699
Plus, telling a dinosaur that
you met your husband online,

13:33.709 --> 13:35.458
doesn't have quite
the same effect.

13:35.542 --> 13:37.789
Now, speaking of which,

13:37.800 --> 13:39.959
can I create an online
dating profile for you?

13:40.041 --> 13:41.333
I don't trust people online.

13:41.956 --> 13:45.333
They lie, and they'll say
anything to get you to meet them,

13:45.417 --> 13:47.125
and then when you do,

13:47.208 --> 13:48.714
it's a big disappointment.

13:49.083 --> 13:50.461
You ever tried it?

13:50.472 --> 13:51.834
I don't need to.

13:51.917 --> 13:53.375
I've seen 20/20.

13:53.458 --> 13:56.133
Hold a sec, you and
Brandon have a history.

13:56.144 --> 13:56.816
Yeah.

13:56.827 --> 13:58.130
Well, he's single now,

13:58.141 --> 13:59.607
and you're kind of whatever,

13:59.618 --> 14:01.439
so why don't you guys pick
up where you left off?

14:01.449 --> 14:03.783
I don't want a relationship.

14:04.625 --> 14:05.709
I'm happy.

14:07.166 --> 14:08.745
Why doesn't anyone believe me?

14:08.756 --> 14:10.625
You are in a
relationship, with Brandon,

14:10.709 --> 14:13.014
you just don't see it.

14:14.375 --> 14:16.542
You guys go to concerts
and movies together,

14:16.625 --> 14:19.704
you do lunches and dinners,
you're practically best friends,

14:19.715 --> 14:21.514
you're just not having sex.

14:22.291 --> 14:25.139
Oh, um,

14:25.375 --> 14:26.959
was he bad in bed?

14:27.041 --> 14:28.959
(tribal drumming)

14:38.798 --> 14:40.009
So, great in bed,

14:40.020 --> 14:42.611
and a dear friend,

14:42.917 --> 14:44.542
what's the problem?

14:44.625 --> 14:47.264
Well, he's never shown any
interest in being with me.

14:47.275 --> 14:48.834
I don't think that's true.

14:48.917 --> 14:50.208
The entire time I've known him,

14:50.291 --> 14:52.125
we've only been together once,

14:52.208 --> 14:54.908
at his house, and he
was still married.

14:54.955 --> 14:57.125
(phone ringing)

14:57.208 --> 14:58.490
That's my wife.

14:58.501 --> 14:59.531
I know it, don't move.

14:59.542 --> 15:00.642
Don't say a word.

15:00.653 --> 15:04.444
Wait until I'm out of
bed before you answer that.

15:09.375 --> 15:09.750
Hello?

15:09.834 --> 15:10.954
[Wife] Hi.

15:11.051 --> 15:12.117
Hey hon.

15:12.128 --> 15:13.615
[Wife] Guess who
caught an early train.

15:13.625 --> 15:14.792
I need you to pick me up.

15:14.875 --> 15:15.792
Where are you?

15:15.875 --> 15:18.019
[Wife] In town at the station.

15:18.030 --> 15:20.113
I love that.

15:20.169 --> 15:21.836
All right, I'll be there in 20.

15:25.509 --> 15:27.125
You went to his house?

15:27.208 --> 15:28.542
That's not like you.

15:28.625 --> 15:31.000
Well, I wasn't as
careful then as I am now.

15:31.011 --> 15:33.428
(rock music)

15:42.959 --> 15:45.590
(phone ringing)

15:45.609 --> 15:46.359
Hello?

15:46.380 --> 15:47.872
I left my earrings there.

15:47.883 --> 15:49.754
Okay, where'd you put them?

15:49.778 --> 15:52.856
They're on the nightstand
on your side of the bed.

15:53.064 --> 15:53.989
Okay, I got 'em.

15:54.000 --> 15:55.317
What do I do with these?

15:55.328 --> 15:56.740
Do you have a place
you can hide them?

15:56.750 --> 15:58.394
Just give them to me
when I see you again.

15:58.405 --> 16:00.322
When Rachel comes home
from a trip, she nests.

16:00.333 --> 16:02.834
She goes through things
and reorganizes everything.

16:02.917 --> 16:03.917
All right.

16:04.750 --> 16:06.528
Do you have a gift box?

16:11.583 --> 16:13.375
Yeah, I got one.

16:13.981 --> 16:14.981
And a ribbon?

16:16.845 --> 16:17.961
I got a bow.

16:17.972 --> 16:19.618
Well, if that's all
you've got, then sure.

16:19.667 --> 16:21.041
Hey what am I doing with these?

16:21.125 --> 16:23.041
Put the earrings in the box.

16:24.000 --> 16:26.155
Wait, am I giving your
earrings to my wife as a gift?

16:26.166 --> 16:27.916
And tell her you
were thinking about her

16:27.927 --> 16:29.437
while she was gone.

16:30.838 --> 16:32.713
That's probably gonna work.

16:32.724 --> 16:33.932
You're the best.

16:34.096 --> 16:35.096
Are we good?

16:35.959 --> 16:36.959
Take a breath.

16:38.458 --> 16:39.458
Go get her.

16:42.417 --> 16:45.121
Lucky for him they
were my good earrings.

16:46.083 --> 16:48.291
So that's why you don't
go to their houses anymore?

16:48.375 --> 16:49.959
Well, that's just one reason.

16:50.041 --> 16:51.453
(bell ringing)

16:51.464 --> 16:53.870
I have a delivery
for Veronica Malloy.

16:54.792 --> 16:55.917
Who are they from?

16:56.000 --> 16:58.041
Card's inside, sign here please.

16:58.125 --> 16:59.125
Okay.

17:01.388 --> 17:03.012
Thank you.

17:05.333 --> 17:06.709
Hmm, beautiful.

17:12.415 --> 17:14.832
Here, for Steve.

17:15.789 --> 17:16.973
What, no likey?

17:16.992 --> 17:19.406
Oh, they should be with somebody
who can actually enjoy them.

17:19.416 --> 17:20.750
Okay, thanks, but

17:20.834 --> 17:22.458
why aren't you enjoying them?

17:22.541 --> 17:26.541
Because they cause more problems
than they actually solve.

17:26.625 --> 17:27.625
Trust me.

17:29.834 --> 17:32.875
(soft piano music)

17:44.709 --> 17:47.896
Veronica, can I get you
anything else this evening?

17:47.959 --> 17:50.005
What about a creme brulee?

17:50.194 --> 17:51.777
What's the occasion?

17:52.166 --> 17:53.497
Just because.

17:53.669 --> 17:54.959
Coming right up.

17:55.041 --> 17:56.125
Thank you.

18:05.250 --> 18:06.250
Hey sweetie.

18:07.112 --> 18:08.607
Oh baby.

18:09.792 --> 18:11.041
And what is for dinner?

18:11.125 --> 18:12.500
Smells fantastic.

18:13.417 --> 18:16.583
My newest creation,
mondiale amore.

18:17.182 --> 18:18.806
Okay.

18:19.875 --> 18:21.542
Oh honey, that is delicious.

18:21.553 --> 18:23.156
Yeah, I'm gonna put
it on the fall menu,

18:23.166 --> 18:25.354
I think the owners
are gonna love it.

18:25.365 --> 18:27.531
Well they are
crazy if they don't.

18:29.505 --> 18:33.177
Oh there's what you got for me.

18:35.041 --> 18:37.502
Geez, must have
cost you a fortune.

18:37.513 --> 18:39.692
Actually, it's a re-gift.

18:41.625 --> 18:43.906
One of Veronica's suitors is
trying to buy her affections.

18:44.677 --> 18:45.790
How is our girl?

18:45.801 --> 18:46.982
She's fine.

18:46.993 --> 18:49.277
Oh and by the way, the loved
the pastries you sent over.

18:49.288 --> 18:52.373
Of course she did, they
were wonderful pastries.

18:54.291 --> 18:56.280
Actually, I'm a little
concerned about her.

18:56.291 --> 18:57.291
Here, wine.

18:57.302 --> 18:58.302
Yes.

18:58.959 --> 19:01.542
I want her to have what we have.

19:01.625 --> 19:04.151
But if she continues down
the road that she's on,

19:04.162 --> 19:05.333
she's never gonna find it.

19:05.417 --> 19:07.375
You need to be a
supportive friend,

19:07.458 --> 19:10.795
and leave her alone, she
needs to find her own way.

19:10.873 --> 19:13.561
But why can't she and
Brandon be together?

19:13.572 --> 19:15.840
Come on, they're
perfect, they fit.

19:16.333 --> 19:17.333
Don't meddle.

19:17.877 --> 19:19.416
Go get washed up.

19:19.515 --> 19:21.848
Dinner is almost ready.

19:21.971 --> 19:24.962
Oh and take down the
sling, it's getting dusty.

19:24.973 --> 19:27.642
[Trent] I told my
mom it's a hammock.

19:27.833 --> 19:29.127
You're kidding.

19:34.333 --> 19:36.083
I'm not going to Tokyo.

19:37.848 --> 19:39.905
I'm sorry, did the
deal fall through?

19:39.916 --> 19:41.987
No, everything's
still on course,

19:41.998 --> 19:45.457
but there are more pressing
issues here at home.

19:48.122 --> 19:50.623
Andrea lost her job last week.

19:51.041 --> 19:54.748
She's devastated, and I want
to be there for her right now.

19:55.001 --> 19:57.460
It's not like we
need the money but,

19:57.583 --> 20:00.385
this is something that
was important to her.

20:06.545 --> 20:07.963
You know when we first met

20:08.041 --> 20:09.481
you said you had to
be there for her,

20:10.307 --> 20:12.307
and now you want to be there.

20:12.318 --> 20:13.775
It's nice to hear.

20:14.646 --> 20:16.479
I hope this isn't goodbye.

20:16.875 --> 20:18.625
Nathan, it would make me happy

20:18.709 --> 20:20.564
if I never heard from you again.

20:21.041 --> 20:22.603
Gee, thanks.

20:22.814 --> 20:24.364
Honey, if I do it
means that there's

20:24.375 --> 20:27.375
something wrong in your marriage,
and you're not fixing it.

20:28.876 --> 20:31.971
Affairs are like drugs,
they can become addictive.

20:32.458 --> 20:33.783
But at the base,

20:34.710 --> 20:36.572
you're just using it
to escape problems

20:36.583 --> 20:38.486
that you don't want to face.

20:39.000 --> 20:40.500
I will miss you.

20:42.500 --> 20:43.500
Be happy.

20:48.458 --> 20:51.417
(solemn piano music)

20:57.445 --> 21:01.458
So, Steve introduced me
to something new last night.

21:01.542 --> 21:03.875
Trent, we've already
discussed oversharing.

21:03.959 --> 21:05.242
New recipe.

21:05.257 --> 21:07.291
Oh, is it good?

21:07.375 --> 21:08.792
Ah, to die for.

21:08.875 --> 21:11.387
I'm telling you, that
man can really cook.

21:11.398 --> 21:13.166
(bell ringing)

21:13.250 --> 21:15.859
Oh, good morning Adam.

21:16.166 --> 21:17.734
Still straight, Trent.

21:17.802 --> 21:18.968
Still married.

21:20.215 --> 21:21.280
For you.

21:21.291 --> 21:22.500
Thank you.

21:22.583 --> 21:23.943
Oh, and I've got
something for you.

21:28.917 --> 21:29.917
Thank you.

21:30.320 --> 21:33.855
Well, I guess I'll see
you at the next sale?

21:34.435 --> 21:35.660
Wait a second.

21:36.080 --> 21:37.430
Aren't you forgetting something?

21:37.441 --> 21:39.041
What's that?

21:39.125 --> 21:40.709
You made me a promise.

21:40.792 --> 21:41.792
Did I?

21:42.891 --> 21:44.682
Really?

21:44.984 --> 21:45.984
Remind me.

21:46.008 --> 21:47.924
Well, if I have to remind you,

21:48.125 --> 21:50.542
clearly it's not that
important to you.

21:50.625 --> 21:51.743
I guess you're right.

21:51.754 --> 21:52.868
About what?

21:52.879 --> 21:54.918
We met over a year ago,

21:54.929 --> 21:57.038
and I've been ridiculous so,

21:57.049 --> 21:58.674
I don't want to
bother you anymore.

21:58.959 --> 22:00.460
So?

22:00.788 --> 22:03.333
So, I give up.

22:04.291 --> 22:05.615
Well I guess I
won't be seeing you

22:05.625 --> 22:07.661
for drinks later tonight.

22:08.125 --> 22:10.667
Okay, and I guess
I won't see you

22:10.750 --> 22:13.542
at that bar at 5th
and Elm at eight.

22:13.625 --> 22:16.834
Hey, I'm not standing
up here for my health.

22:16.979 --> 22:18.479
Oh I'm sorry.

22:20.667 --> 22:22.625
See you later.

22:22.709 --> 22:23.792
You know it.

22:28.192 --> 22:31.317
Ronnie, you just went through
a breakup two hours ago.

22:31.378 --> 22:34.253
Don't you think you need
a little time to heal?

22:34.500 --> 22:35.785
Heal from what?

22:36.158 --> 22:38.322
My relationships always
have an expiration date.

22:38.333 --> 22:40.500
It's a matter of when, not if.

22:42.661 --> 22:45.629
And you don't see
anything wrong with that?

22:47.241 --> 22:49.158
Okay, you know what
your problem is?

22:49.169 --> 22:51.961
You're emotionally
claustrophobic.

22:52.088 --> 22:54.464
Look, I'm not looking
for a relationship.

22:55.302 --> 22:57.489
Lord knows the drama
that comes with one,

22:57.500 --> 22:59.949
I have right here with you.

23:00.198 --> 23:01.198
Oh, okay.

23:04.876 --> 23:07.377
(somber orchestral music)

23:42.599 --> 23:44.390
Gorgeous.

23:44.636 --> 23:46.542
Thank you.

23:46.625 --> 23:48.792
Sorry I'm late, life.

23:49.753 --> 23:51.333
Excuse me, sir.

23:51.417 --> 23:52.417
Scotch neat, please.

23:54.814 --> 23:56.439
So, tell me,

23:57.417 --> 23:59.345
what changed your mind?

24:01.000 --> 24:03.103
I wasn't available until now.

24:04.183 --> 24:05.183
Oh, I see.

24:05.959 --> 24:09.083
Well I'm sorry it
didn't work out.

24:09.166 --> 24:12.614
That's the last lie you're
ever going to tell me.

24:12.918 --> 24:14.543
Thank you.

24:14.953 --> 24:16.254
(phone notification)

24:16.754 --> 24:18.000
Excuse me.

24:18.489 --> 24:19.489
Sure.

24:29.752 --> 24:33.035
Are you okay with the
fact that I'm not yours,

24:33.055 --> 24:34.567
and I never will be.

24:34.834 --> 24:37.917
I know my place and
I'm comfortable with it.

24:38.000 --> 24:40.000
Else, I wouldn't be here.

24:40.619 --> 24:42.231
Cheers?

24:42.799 --> 24:43.799
Cheers.

24:48.875 --> 24:51.231
Are you seeing anyone else?

24:51.903 --> 24:53.570
Aside from my wife?

24:53.834 --> 24:54.834
No.

24:55.837 --> 24:57.478
Let me lay it out for you now.

24:57.489 --> 24:59.115
Do, please.

25:00.078 --> 25:02.535
I have been mad about
you since the day we met,

25:02.546 --> 25:04.671
and I can't stop
thinking about you.

25:05.617 --> 25:07.451
I'm not leaving my wife.

25:08.833 --> 25:10.958
But I have to be with you.

25:12.004 --> 25:15.171
(romantic piano music)

26:32.351 --> 26:34.947
You are very quiet this morning.

26:36.583 --> 26:39.939
I just wish someone knew
how I really want it to be.

26:40.375 --> 26:41.375
Do tell.

26:42.164 --> 26:44.916
Well, I know it
sounds selfish but,

26:46.250 --> 26:47.530
there are times
when I wish a guy

26:47.583 --> 26:48.875
would pay attention to my needs

26:48.959 --> 26:51.392
as much as he pays
attention to his.

26:52.809 --> 26:54.663
So, safe to say that Adam

26:54.674 --> 26:57.319
will only be filling
our shelves from now on.

26:57.330 --> 26:59.260
No, I don't know about that.

26:59.417 --> 27:01.500
Look, what you need,

27:01.583 --> 27:04.291
is a guy that isn't
splitting his focus,

27:05.179 --> 27:06.679
like Brandon.

27:07.375 --> 27:09.000
Trent, you know me,

27:09.083 --> 27:12.650
as soon as I get into a
relationship I push them away.

27:12.661 --> 27:15.056
It's how I'm wired,
it's who I am.

27:15.155 --> 27:17.864
And I don't want to
do that to Brandon.

27:17.875 --> 27:19.375
Well if Brandon is any evidence

27:19.458 --> 27:20.667
of how you push people away,

27:20.750 --> 27:24.041
then you my dear
are very bad at it.

27:24.125 --> 27:26.500
I tried, he just wouldn't leave.

27:27.875 --> 27:30.076
He just stuck in there and,

27:31.607 --> 27:33.927
I've grown to love
our friendship.

27:35.169 --> 27:38.250
But that was him, it's all him.

27:38.333 --> 27:41.417
So I guess we are
back to square one.

27:50.125 --> 27:52.458
(rock music)

27:56.171 --> 27:58.796
Well, can we see this
when we're up there?

28:00.062 --> 28:01.931
Oh, butterflies.

28:03.717 --> 28:05.736
It's gonna add a couple
hours to our trip.

28:05.747 --> 28:07.845
I'm not in any
hurry to get back.

28:09.023 --> 28:10.398
All right, we'll see.

28:10.513 --> 28:14.179
♪ When I look at you ♪

28:14.364 --> 28:17.740
♪ It makes my
heart skip a beat ♪

28:17.917 --> 28:21.667
♪ I don't know what to do ♪

28:21.750 --> 28:23.750
♪ I know what I want ♪

28:23.834 --> 28:25.834
♪ And baby it's you ♪

28:25.917 --> 28:28.417
♪ Imagine the things we'd do ♪

28:28.500 --> 28:31.542
♪ Won't try to make decisions ♪

28:31.625 --> 28:37.583
♪ Without a lot of indecision ♪

28:38.625 --> 28:43.166
♪ Baby what would you
do if you were mine ♪

28:45.375 --> 28:48.041
♪ All mine ♪

28:48.125 --> 28:53.041
♪ I want you want you
want you be mine ♪

28:53.125 --> 28:58.000
♪ Baby be mine ♪

28:59.542 --> 29:02.875
♪ Somebody told me that you
were a major possibility ♪

29:04.291 --> 29:05.834
(thunder)

29:05.917 --> 29:08.625
♪ A second time now
that we both know ♪

29:08.709 --> 29:14.250
♪ Gonna make it
with ahead of me ♪

29:14.333 --> 29:18.041
♪ I know what I want
and baby it's you ♪

29:18.125 --> 29:23.208
♪ Imagine the things we'll
do won't try a new position ♪

29:24.000 --> 29:29.583
♪ A lot of lot of indecision. ♪

29:30.834 --> 29:35.208
♪ Baby what would you
