29:44.333 --> 29:46.959
♪ Baby be mine ♪

30:06.166 --> 30:11.166
♪ Baby what would you
do if you were mine ♪

30:14.583 --> 30:19.583
♪ Baby what would you
do if you were mine ♪

30:20.959 --> 30:23.917
♪ Be mine, won't you be mine ♪

30:24.000 --> 30:29.500
♪ Won't you won't you
won't you be mine ♪

30:29.583 --> 30:33.875
♪ Baby be mine ♪

30:33.959 --> 30:37.542
♪ Just be mine ♪

30:37.625 --> 30:40.208
♪ Baby be mine ♪

30:41.651 --> 30:42.651
Hi.

30:43.336 --> 30:44.836
Hi, sleepy head.

30:46.591 --> 30:47.798
Where are we?

30:48.680 --> 30:51.057
Come on, I'll show you.

30:54.166 --> 30:58.000
(gentle piano and flute music)

31:04.679 --> 31:07.137
Oh my God, the butterflies.

31:08.511 --> 31:09.511
Thank you.

31:11.156 --> 31:13.155
Now I feel bad about
falling asleep.

31:13.166 --> 31:15.120
I wanted to surprise you.

31:18.612 --> 31:21.041
I wonder how many
butterflies come here.

31:21.125 --> 31:22.458
I don't know about that,

31:22.542 --> 31:25.706
but at least 100,000
humans come here each year.

31:26.583 --> 31:28.253
This is unbelievable.

31:28.401 --> 31:30.628
Did you know that
these butterflies

31:30.661 --> 31:33.253
have a lifespan of six months,

31:33.264 --> 31:36.765
whereas the common monarch
only lives for six weeks.

31:39.017 --> 31:40.017
Wow.

31:42.140 --> 31:43.765
Say cheese.

31:44.000 --> 31:45.120
Cheese.

31:49.672 --> 31:50.672
Oh it's pretty.

31:51.914 --> 31:52.914
Wow.

32:11.674 --> 32:14.250
Hey, your clothes,
can we move them?

32:14.261 --> 32:15.261
That's my bed.

32:16.004 --> 32:17.296
Sorry.

32:17.583 --> 32:18.834
Hey, you hungry?

32:18.917 --> 32:19.901
Yeah, I could eat.

32:19.912 --> 32:20.537
You want to go out or you want
to get something delivered?

32:20.548 --> 32:21.369
Let's order something in,

32:21.435 --> 32:23.721
then we can watch a movie on TV.

32:24.583 --> 32:25.874
Oh, that's a good idea.

32:25.885 --> 32:28.000
I'm sure there's a
pizza place close by.

32:28.083 --> 32:29.321
God, not pizza.

32:29.332 --> 32:31.416
You love pizza.

32:31.869 --> 32:33.744
I've eaten a lot lately.

32:35.606 --> 32:36.606
Okay well,

32:37.445 --> 32:40.094
I guess that only
leaves us one option.

32:56.861 --> 32:58.320
Dinner is served.

33:00.624 --> 33:03.115
And don't say anything, you
wanted to see the butterflies,

33:03.125 --> 33:04.708
so that's what you get.

33:05.062 --> 33:06.900
Otherwise you would
have been home by now.

33:06.911 --> 33:08.447
Well, it was worth it.

33:08.458 --> 33:09.782
I know you're
used to fine cuisine

33:09.792 --> 33:11.885
at five-star hotels,

33:11.896 --> 33:14.166
but this is as good
as it's gonna get.

33:14.177 --> 33:15.177
What do you got there?

33:15.188 --> 33:16.429
Rollos?

33:16.440 --> 33:17.856
Maybe.

33:20.417 --> 33:21.417
Okay, catch.

33:22.667 --> 33:23.667
Thanks.

33:27.698 --> 33:29.446
Can I ask you something?

33:29.509 --> 33:31.759
Yeah, anything, what?

33:31.919 --> 33:35.149
I get the VIP treatment,
and the fancy nights out.

33:35.875 --> 33:38.917
What do you see in these
guys that you go out with?

33:39.000 --> 33:40.875
Well, they fit into my schedule,

33:40.959 --> 33:43.517
and they don't ask questions.

33:43.765 --> 33:45.515
Is that enough for you?

33:45.834 --> 33:47.500
Well, it has been so far.

33:49.333 --> 33:51.166
I like my independence,
I liked deciding

33:51.250 --> 33:53.542
what I want to do and when,

33:53.867 --> 33:57.290
and I like having the freedom
of not being tied down.

33:57.460 --> 33:58.479
So that's it?

33:58.490 --> 33:59.583
Yeah, that's it.

33:59.667 --> 34:01.083
I like my life the way it is.

34:01.166 --> 34:02.667
It's not complicated.

34:03.973 --> 34:07.114
And besides the most honest
relationships I've ever had,

34:07.125 --> 34:09.333
have been when I've
been a mistress.

34:09.417 --> 34:10.435
But...

34:11.529 --> 34:14.654
don't you want
emotional intimacy?

34:15.101 --> 34:18.337
I know you, you have the
most beautiful soul Veronica.

34:18.348 --> 34:20.389
I just don't get it.

34:20.679 --> 34:23.304
I have just learned
not to need it.

34:23.315 --> 34:24.690
Besides I have friends for that.

34:24.699 --> 34:26.851
I have Trent, I have you.

34:26.918 --> 34:28.001
And I have Steve.

34:28.012 --> 34:29.969
So it's all about the
physical with these men?

34:30.041 --> 34:32.376
No, it's about
making my life easier.

34:33.208 --> 34:34.458
I don't have to invest.

34:34.542 --> 34:36.668
I can walk away when I want to.

34:36.679 --> 34:38.375
Well, that's a pretty
pathetic way to live.

34:38.458 --> 34:40.944
I mean sure maybe you don't
get hurt along the way,

34:40.955 --> 34:42.562
but years from now?

34:44.036 --> 34:45.155
Don't you judge me,

34:45.166 --> 34:46.833
I mean you fix your insecurities

34:46.917 --> 34:49.000
with the occasional
woman who feeds your ego,

34:49.083 --> 34:53.250
and I fix mine by not letting
anyone know all about me.

34:53.333 --> 34:55.053
I mean we're basically
doing the same thing,

34:55.083 --> 34:56.291
but in different ways.

34:57.817 --> 34:59.333
And yes, it can get tiresome

34:59.417 --> 35:01.924
to always have to
stay on my game but,

35:02.041 --> 35:03.875
beats the alternative.

35:03.886 --> 35:05.739
And the alternative is what?

35:05.750 --> 35:07.834
Having a meaningful,
valuable relationship

35:07.917 --> 35:09.709
with a man that
you're intimate with?

35:10.929 --> 35:14.262
Look I know, I've been
guilty of feeding my ego.

35:15.341 --> 35:18.258
But in the meantime, I know
deep down what I really want.

35:18.269 --> 35:19.656
Do you think for a second

35:19.667 --> 35:21.452
there haven't been some
of these one-nighters

35:21.463 --> 35:23.750
that I didn't have some
hope that maybe, just maybe,

35:23.761 --> 35:25.674
I'd meet somebody special?

35:27.188 --> 35:28.188
No.

35:28.351 --> 35:29.934
No?

35:30.334 --> 35:32.014
To me, the alternative's
being vulnerable

35:32.025 --> 35:34.900
and being vulnerable,
vulnerable people get hurt,

35:34.924 --> 35:38.111
and I just don't want
that to happen to me.

35:39.185 --> 35:41.614
And are you really so
deluded that you think

35:41.625 --> 35:44.669
that a one-night stand
could be any more than that?

35:44.680 --> 35:46.102
By very definition
it's nothing more

35:46.113 --> 35:47.197
than a one-night affair.

35:47.208 --> 35:49.542
I'm not trying to
pick a fight with you.

35:49.625 --> 35:51.931
We just have never had
this discussion before.

35:51.959 --> 35:53.936
I'm just trying to understand.

35:53.947 --> 35:56.739
Chalk it up to being
a better friend.

35:56.750 --> 35:58.041
And you're right,

35:58.125 --> 35:59.709
a one-night stand is just that.

36:01.080 --> 36:04.142
I've just never known
anyone like you, that's all.

36:05.036 --> 36:06.537
And since we're sharing,

36:06.548 --> 36:08.693
why don't you tell me the
story about your divorce,

36:08.704 --> 36:10.743
and why haven't
you ever told me?

36:14.004 --> 36:18.102
Well, we met in
photography school,

36:19.306 --> 36:20.595
and...

36:21.382 --> 36:22.465
as soon as we graduated

36:22.476 --> 36:24.498
we really struggled
to find work.

36:25.502 --> 36:27.489
But I just kept feeding
my passion for shooting

36:27.500 --> 36:29.083
landscapes and coastlines,

36:29.166 --> 36:31.417
and in the process
I built a career,

36:31.500 --> 36:33.583
but she was still floundering.

36:33.667 --> 36:35.959
She couldn't find
her voice, you know?

36:36.041 --> 36:38.903
Well that's a dangerous
place for an artist.

36:38.927 --> 36:40.875
And time went on and,

36:40.959 --> 36:43.709
I was being published, and
her career was stagnant and,

36:44.616 --> 36:47.366
more and more, she just
wouldn't even look at my work,

36:47.959 --> 36:49.583
like she resented me.

36:51.190 --> 36:53.263
I think she fell out of
love with photography,

36:53.274 --> 36:56.700
and in the process, fell
out of love with me also.

36:59.289 --> 37:00.614
It's sad.

37:00.833 --> 37:02.850
The one thing that brought
the two of you together,

37:02.861 --> 37:05.434
is the one thing
that drove you apart.

37:12.542 --> 37:14.750
And I didn't tell you because,

37:16.542 --> 37:19.630
even though you weren't
the cause of my divorce,

37:21.625 --> 37:23.959
you were definitely a symptom

37:25.417 --> 37:27.770
of the erosion of
my partnership.

37:34.917 --> 37:36.666
What are we gonna watch?

37:36.677 --> 37:37.689
Hitchcock.

37:37.700 --> 37:39.983
Hitchcock, he made
a lot of movies.

37:39.994 --> 37:42.244
Hitchcock, the movie.

37:42.575 --> 37:44.667
You'll like it.

37:44.750 --> 37:47.041
I think it has nudity in it.

37:47.125 --> 37:48.599
Scooch over.

37:52.750 --> 37:53.750
You ready.

37:58.750 --> 38:00.959
(screaming)

38:06.583 --> 38:07.740
[Man On TV]
<i>Darling, we've watched</i>

38:07.750 --> 38:09.458
<i>the film a hundred times.</i>

38:09.542 --> 38:11.031
<i>She doesn't blink.</i>

38:11.792 --> 38:12.792
What?

38:13.583 --> 38:14.583
Nothing.

38:16.136 --> 38:17.761
Okay.

38:20.197 --> 38:21.822
What?

38:22.595 --> 38:25.595
Nothing, shhh watch the movie.

38:34.839 --> 38:37.166
<i>[Man On TV] So with
very little effort,</i>

38:37.250 --> 38:39.834
<i>and the reflex time
of a garden snail,</i>

38:39.917 --> 38:43.417
<i>how does a tortoise's
day compare to ours?</i>

38:43.500 --> 38:46.500
<i>In the time it takes
us to drive 10 miles,</i>

38:46.583 --> 38:49.583
<i>the tortoise manages
to move about 100 feet.</i>

38:50.542 --> 38:52.750
<i>While we eat an entire meal,</i>

38:52.834 --> 38:54.959
<i>he has nibbled on
some vegetation.</i>

38:56.000 --> 38:59.417
<i>And as we spend a day
filming another sequence,</i>

38:59.500 --> 39:01.870
<i>for him, it's time for a nap.</i>

39:02.378 --> 39:04.792
<i>The tortoise's way of
making up for that,</i>

39:04.875 --> 39:08.083
<i>isn't to eat more,
but to do less.</i>

39:10.744 --> 39:13.494
(soft piano music)

39:23.500 --> 39:26.166
(phone buzzing)

39:37.215 --> 39:39.841
(door closing)

39:42.375 --> 39:44.292
Good morning, sunshine.

39:44.656 --> 39:46.239
Hey.

39:46.518 --> 39:48.188
I know you're like
a bear with a sore paw

39:48.198 --> 39:51.072
when you don't get
your caffeine fix so.

39:51.083 --> 39:52.166
Thanks.

39:52.679 --> 39:55.720
You know they say this
stuff is actually flammable.

39:58.291 --> 39:59.417
You missed a call.

40:00.458 --> 40:01.458
Thanks.

40:02.625 --> 40:04.208
[Phone] Voicemail received.

40:06.375 --> 40:07.458
You should check that.

40:07.542 --> 40:09.750
Yeah, I'm just
gonna brush my teeth,

40:09.834 --> 40:12.583
and then the
bathroom's all yours.

40:18.083 --> 40:20.583
(romantic piano music)

40:38.583 --> 40:39.583
Okay.

40:40.542 --> 40:41.542
You all set?

40:42.875 --> 40:45.380
Why haven't you
told me about her?

40:46.151 --> 40:47.359
Excuse me.

40:47.959 --> 40:48.959
Who's Kristen?

40:50.057 --> 40:52.365
She's just a woman I know, why?

40:53.151 --> 40:55.234
I think it's a little
bit more than that.

40:57.414 --> 40:58.414
Okay.

41:00.458 --> 41:01.667
Seriously, Brandon?

41:03.132 --> 41:05.257
I mean you're not gonna
tell me about her?

41:07.291 --> 41:09.252
I knew it, I knew it,
that day in the store

41:09.263 --> 41:10.682
when you picked up
that text message,

41:10.692 --> 41:11.818
I knew something was up.

41:13.161 --> 41:14.411
Why couldn't you tell me?

41:15.709 --> 41:17.709
What do you want
to hear Veronica?

41:20.125 --> 41:22.904
I saw a picture of
you and her kissing.

41:25.020 --> 41:27.732
Is this new, how long
has it been going on?

41:28.875 --> 41:30.709
So you woke up and
you went to my phone?

41:30.792 --> 41:34.125
No Brandon, the
phone woke me up,

41:34.208 --> 41:36.542
and I was startled
by the picture.

41:36.625 --> 41:38.098
Startled, really?

41:38.109 --> 41:41.276
Isn't that a little
bit extreme, Ronnie?

41:43.917 --> 41:45.667
To wake up in a bed
that I shared with you

41:45.750 --> 41:46.750
to that picture,

41:48.625 --> 41:50.250
you tell me.

41:51.588 --> 41:53.739
We didn't share the bed, Ronnie.

41:54.249 --> 41:56.357
We fell asleep watching a movie.

42:00.507 --> 42:01.507
What?

42:04.369 --> 42:05.369
Just,

42:07.835 --> 42:10.153
just get me home.

42:12.877 --> 42:16.418
(somber orchestral music)

42:38.738 --> 42:40.405
Hi honey.

42:41.166 --> 42:42.792
Hey.

42:42.875 --> 42:43.500
Welcome home, hotshot.

42:43.583 --> 42:46.000
Oh, thank you, sorry I'm late.

42:46.083 --> 42:47.185
Traffic was hell.

42:47.555 --> 42:48.929
Of course.

42:49.250 --> 42:51.333
God I missed you.

42:55.119 --> 42:57.036
Oh, dinner smells great,

42:57.047 --> 42:58.755
and so do you.

43:01.208 --> 43:02.291
What's this?

43:02.375 --> 43:04.959
That is a birthday present
for your grandnephew.

43:05.041 --> 43:07.542
I figured with all the traveling,
you wouldn't have time,

43:07.625 --> 43:09.709
so I picked it up for you.

43:11.583 --> 43:13.083
Thank you.

43:13.166 --> 43:14.563
You are welcome.

43:15.233 --> 43:17.976
Why don't you open up that bottle
of wine right there, do you mind?

43:17.987 --> 43:20.195
I tried but I couldn't.

43:25.083 --> 43:27.239
So, how was the trip?

43:27.921 --> 43:29.671
Got some good shots.

43:29.840 --> 43:32.715
I think the publisher's gonna
like the direction it's going.

43:32.729 --> 43:34.813
Can't wait to see it.

43:43.565 --> 43:44.565
What?

43:45.506 --> 43:46.506
Nothing.

43:50.222 --> 43:51.222
Okay.

43:53.195 --> 43:55.903
Would you mind
lighting the candles?

43:56.518 --> 43:57.518
Sure.

43:58.625 --> 44:00.709
You know how I am with fire.

44:15.083 --> 44:17.634
I can't believe that he's
been seeing her for six months,

44:17.645 --> 44:20.500
and he's never mentioned
her to me, not a word.

44:20.583 --> 44:22.792
I mean, I mean
call me crazy but,

44:22.875 --> 44:25.709
when you know someone
that long and that well,

44:25.792 --> 44:27.543
doesn't it seem odd,

44:27.804 --> 44:30.887
and why has he never
introduced me to her?

44:32.187 --> 44:33.187
I don't care.

44:35.834 --> 44:36.834
Come here.

45:03.750 --> 45:05.250
You are fantastic.

45:08.041 --> 45:09.917
Stay with me tonight.

45:10.000 --> 45:11.250
No.

45:11.333 --> 45:13.375
I'm clear until tomorrow.

45:13.458 --> 45:15.332
She's out of town on business.

45:16.601 --> 45:18.226
I can't.

45:18.872 --> 45:21.206
I don't want to
get used to this.

45:23.709 --> 45:28.000
Well, I guess that's something
I'll have to get used to.

45:34.333 --> 45:37.417
You know there's something
I've been meaning to ask you.

45:37.500 --> 45:40.653
I have a client who's
looking for a rare book,

45:40.664 --> 45:42.996
and we can't seem to find it.

45:43.007 --> 45:44.155
What is it?

45:44.166 --> 45:46.458
It's called the Emerald Whaler,

45:46.469 --> 45:50.010
written by William
J Lowbenstein.

45:52.022 --> 45:53.231
Lubby.

45:53.304 --> 45:54.638
Oh, you've heard of him?

45:55.754 --> 45:56.754
Maybe.

45:58.228 --> 46:02.715
Well, I need a first
edition, 1960, signed copy.

46:03.411 --> 46:05.403
Can you find that for me?

46:05.976 --> 46:07.934
It'll be rare, expensive,

46:09.750 --> 46:11.333
and if I say yes will
that persuade you

46:11.417 --> 46:13.709
to stay with me tonight?

46:13.792 --> 46:14.792
No.

46:17.171 --> 46:19.762
But it'll make me very happy.

46:35.125 --> 46:37.039
Can I help you find something?

46:38.125 --> 46:40.437
Oh hi, yes thank you.

46:41.291 --> 46:43.656
Well I'm looking
for a book about

46:44.250 --> 46:45.667
dating after divorce.

46:45.750 --> 46:48.500
Hmmm, well I'm not
sure reading a book's

46:48.583 --> 46:50.296
really gonna help you.

46:51.783 --> 46:53.945
What would you
look for in a man?

46:54.583 --> 46:56.250
Well that varies actually.

46:57.709 --> 47:00.265
But he doesn't have to
be a saint though, does he?

47:01.250 --> 47:03.715
I tell you what, why don't you
make me a list of attributes

47:03.726 --> 47:07.234
that I might possess, which
will be attractive to a woman,

47:07.245 --> 47:09.328
such as yourself.

47:11.542 --> 47:13.166
Trent.

47:13.250 --> 47:14.598
Need your help.

47:14.638 --> 47:16.291
Someone will come and help you.

47:16.375 --> 47:18.000
I can wait until you're through.

47:19.114 --> 47:20.247
I'm sorry.

47:20.258 --> 47:22.364
No it's just that I've
been married for 30 years,

47:22.375 --> 47:24.934
and now, newly single.

47:25.970 --> 47:28.638
Well, being a gentleman
never goes out of style,

47:28.649 --> 47:32.879
and women love honesty.

47:34.814 --> 47:35.970
Brandon?

47:35.981 --> 47:36.832
Hey.

47:36.843 --> 47:37.843
Hi Trent.

47:42.588 --> 47:44.004
What?

47:44.015 --> 47:46.012
Let me take care of this guy.

47:46.125 --> 47:47.291
Why?

47:47.302 --> 47:48.677
He's cute, he's single,

47:48.688 --> 47:50.615
I thought you'd be thrilled
that I'm talking to him.

47:50.625 --> 47:51.426
He's gay.

47:51.437 --> 47:52.437
No.

47:52.500 --> 47:53.625
Trust me.

47:55.375 --> 47:56.542
He is?

47:56.625 --> 47:58.238
I know it.

47:58.542 --> 48:01.215
Worked it out with
Brandon, he's cuter.

48:02.291 --> 48:03.957
Fine.

48:09.709 --> 48:10.709
Hey.

48:12.247 --> 48:13.247
Seriously?

48:14.041 --> 48:15.291
You pitch a fit up in Pismo

48:15.375 --> 48:17.041
and now you're not
taking my calls.

48:18.000 --> 48:19.125
That sounds about right.

48:19.722 --> 48:22.333
Ronnie, clearly you're
upset, but I haven't a clue--

48:22.417 --> 48:23.959
Don't you understand
why I'm upset?

48:24.041 --> 48:26.750
Please, please,
tell me what exactly

48:26.834 --> 48:28.000
I'm dealing with here.

48:28.083 --> 48:30.125
You lied to me,
you kept secrets.

48:30.136 --> 48:31.041
I lied?

48:31.125 --> 48:32.125
What did I lie about?

48:33.054 --> 48:36.292
Okay, I haven't mentioned
Kristen to you, but lied?

48:36.375 --> 48:37.875
It's a lie by omission.

48:37.959 --> 48:39.041
A what?

48:39.125 --> 48:42.273
If you lead someone
to believe one thing,

48:42.284 --> 48:43.740
based on your words
and your actions

48:43.750 --> 48:46.834
and then it turns out to be
something completely different,

48:46.917 --> 48:48.542
that's a lie.

48:48.625 --> 48:50.333
I still don't get it.

48:50.417 --> 48:51.667
Of course you don't.

48:51.750 --> 48:54.750
I didn't lie, I
just didn't tell you.

48:54.834 --> 48:57.660
Yeah, well that's just
guys' slight of hand.

48:58.301 --> 48:59.333
Where am I going?

48:59.417 --> 49:00.816
Goodbye Brandon.

49:02.278 --> 49:03.579
We're not done here.

49:03.590 --> 49:04.805
Yes we are.

49:04.816 --> 49:05.777
(bell ringing)

49:05.788 --> 49:07.152
I'll call you later.

49:08.985 --> 49:11.409
He didn't
technically lie to you.

49:11.934 --> 49:13.899
Don't you start now.

49:13.910 --> 49:16.333
Veronica, he doesn't
owe you anything.

49:16.417 --> 49:18.792
He owes me respect.

49:18.875 --> 49:22.000
I couldn't care less that
he's seeing somebody,

49:22.083 --> 49:23.697
but hiding it from me?

49:23.708 --> 49:25.959
Telling somebody that
you've never lied,

49:26.041 --> 49:28.333
just because someone hasn't
asked a specific question,

49:28.417 --> 49:30.723
doesn't somehow make the truth.

49:39.797 --> 49:42.542
Wasn't Trent fantastic
the other night?

49:42.625 --> 49:43.625
Oh, the show was great.

49:43.709 --> 49:45.542
I'm so proud of you.

49:45.625 --> 49:47.417
Thank you, not too blue?

49:47.500 --> 49:49.542
No.

49:49.553 --> 49:51.387
Well, you did push the
envelope a little bit,

49:51.398 --> 49:53.414
but yeah, it was really good.

49:53.425 --> 49:55.773
Why didn't you do your
bit about the royal family?

49:55.784 --> 49:58.041
Well I like to think
I have a little more

49:58.125 --> 49:59.542
originality than that.

49:59.625 --> 50:00.458
Huh.

50:00.542 --> 50:02.000
Huh?

50:02.083 --> 50:03.375
You know I was laughing so much

50:03.458 --> 50:05.792
I had tears rolling
down my cheeks.

50:05.875 --> 50:06.750
Really?

50:06.834 --> 50:08.583
You know you should
do more comedy.

50:08.667 --> 50:10.709
I think you may have
missed your calling.

50:11.208 --> 50:12.472
Maybe I will.

50:12.483 --> 50:14.333
(phone ringing)

50:17.208 --> 50:19.010
Still not speaking with him?

50:19.073 --> 50:19.784
No.

50:19.795 --> 50:21.416
- Who?
- Brandon.

50:21.908 --> 50:23.364
What did he do now?

50:23.375 --> 50:25.375
Well he didn't
do anything wrong.

50:25.458 --> 50:27.440
You tell it, what did he do?

50:28.166 --> 50:31.250
Is a lie by omission a
lie, or is it the truth?

50:32.333 --> 50:34.208
But there's no truth in a lie.

50:34.291 --> 50:36.750
But it's not a lie if no
one actually said anything.

50:36.761 --> 50:38.276
Schschm...

50:38.666 --> 50:41.823
Is what Brandon didn't tell you,

50:41.930 --> 50:45.472
not said maybe to
spare your feelings?

50:45.542 --> 50:48.125
Look it doesn't
matter how I feel.

50:48.208 --> 50:49.625
I thought we were
closer than that,

50:49.709 --> 50:52.000
I thought we could tell
each other everything.

50:53.166 --> 50:56.625
Now I, I don't
trust him anymore.

50:57.336 --> 51:00.182
Bring me up to speed here.

51:00.552 --> 51:02.114
Okay, here's what happened.

51:02.125 --> 51:04.366
Ronnie found out that Brandon
has been seeing someone.

51:04.377 --> 51:05.245
So?

51:05.256 --> 51:06.964
For over six months?

51:07.168 --> 51:10.460
Oh honey, he has
feelings for you.

51:10.475 --> 51:12.940
He's been single
for almost five years.

51:12.959 --> 51:14.948
He's never made a move on me.

51:14.959 --> 51:17.448
He's never even offered
me any kind of affection,

51:17.459 --> 51:19.327
other than friendship.

51:19.338 --> 51:21.445
And we've always had this
open line of communication

51:21.456 --> 51:23.500
when it comes to dating.

51:23.511 --> 51:26.595
I mean, we practically
tell each other everything.

51:26.606 --> 51:29.690
So you were closer with
Brandon than anyone else?

51:29.701 --> 51:31.070
Don't you think it's kind of odd

51:31.080 --> 51:33.291
that you haven't
found a relationship?

51:33.375 --> 51:37.166
Maybe he's just filling the gap
of what you expect from men?

51:37.250 --> 51:39.625
Look, we all know,
everyone knows,

51:39.636 --> 51:41.929
that the two of you have
feelings for each other.

51:41.940 --> 51:43.834
Maybe he didn't tell
you about the girl

51:43.917 --> 51:45.458
because he knew it
would affect you.

51:45.542 --> 51:48.083
No, I would have been
fine if he'd told me.

51:49.529 --> 51:51.779
Really, I want him to be happy.

51:51.790 --> 51:53.073
Then why are you
ignoring his calls

51:53.083 --> 51:54.674
instead of celebrating with him.

51:54.705 --> 51:56.484
Let's do a little
survey shall we?

51:56.495 --> 51:57.834
Oh yes, let's.

51:57.845 --> 51:59.303
Mm-hmmm.

51:59.314 --> 52:02.356
When you're not with Brandon,
do you think about him?

52:02.583 --> 52:03.583
Yes.

52:04.484 --> 52:06.109
But I also think about Trent.

52:06.583 --> 52:07.875
Okay, fair enough.

52:07.959 --> 52:13.000
Where did Brandon have
lunch last Monday?

52:13.512 --> 52:14.987
Piccolo Paradisio.

52:15.065 --> 52:17.731
Where did Trent
have lunch yesterday?

52:18.886 --> 52:22.041
I didn't have lunch, I
stayed in the store, remember?

52:23.158 --> 52:24.377
I've got one.

52:24.388 --> 52:26.721
Who do you call when you
need help with something?

52:27.208 --> 52:27.959
Brandon.

52:28.041 --> 52:30.440
Mm-hmm, and yet I'm closer.

52:30.854 --> 52:32.843
[Steve] Do you answer his texts

52:32.854 --> 52:34.417
when you're with someone else?

52:34.500 --> 52:35.875
Sometimes, it depends.

52:35.959 --> 52:37.125
Mm-hmm, depends.

52:37.208 --> 52:39.542
Where does Brandon
get his hair cut?

52:39.625 --> 52:41.276
Oh, the Last Tango.

52:41.287 --> 52:42.960
Karen's been his girl for years.

52:42.971 --> 52:44.959
Where does Trent
get his hair cut?

52:45.702 --> 52:47.114
I cut his hair.

52:47.125 --> 52:47.834
I knew that.

52:47.917 --> 52:49.375
Bullshit.

52:49.458 --> 52:52.583
Can he answer all those
questions about you?

52:52.667 --> 52:54.031
Um, most of them,
but probably not

